OOPs with book example
Uses a base class "Book"
Created two sub classes : "Novel" and "Comic"
Use a function 'read_book()'
Encapsulation - varibles like _title and _author
Inheritance - "Novel" and "Comic" from book
Polymorphism - read_book() function work on both novel and Comic
Abstraction - method names read,get_role
Output
Reading novel:'Harry Potter' by J.K.Rowling
This is a Novel
Enjoying comic:'Spiderman' by Stan Lee
This is a Comic